title: Starmer Slams Trump’s Greenland Tariffs As EU Vows To Defend Against Coercion | 10 News
description: British Prime Minister Keir Starmer has criticised Donald Trump’s plan to impose 10 per cent tariffs on eight European nations over opposition to American control of Greenland, warning a trade war is “completely wrong” and not in anyone’s interest.  Trump has set a February start date for the import tax, escalating tensions with NATO allies after some deployed small numbers of troops to Greenland, which he argues is crucial for a US missile defence system.  Starmer said Britain will keep dialogue open and won’t “pretend differences don’t exist,” but indicated the UK is not considering retaliatory measures.  EU leaders say they are prepared to defend against economic “coercion,” as Denmark and Greenland hold planned talks with NATO officials on Arctic security. title: Spain Train Crash Death Toll Rises To At Least 40 | 10 News

title: 100-Vehicle Pileup Shuts Down Interstate In Michigan Amid Snowstorm | 10 News
description: More than 100 vehicles have been involved in a major pile-up after smashing into each other and sliding off an interstate in Michigan as a winter storm moves across the state.  The massive pileup on Monday morning led the Michigan State Police to close both directions of Interstate 196 while officials worked to remove all the vehicles, including more than 30 semitrailer trucks.  State Police said there were numerous injuries, but no deaths had been reported.  The highway is reportedly closed in both directions as authorities work to clear damaged vehicles.
